# React & TypeScript Patterns

## Type Safety

- Use TypeScript for all new code
- Maintain strict type checking
- Avoid `any` types unless absolutely necessary
- Use proper type imports (`import type` when importing only types)

```tsx
import type { ComponentProps } from 'react'

interface ButtonProps extends ComponentProps<'button'> {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary'
}
```

## Component Composition

Keep components focused and reusable. Follow composition patterns.

```tsx
const Card = ({ children, className }: { children: React.ReactNode; className?: string }) => (
  <div className={cn(s.card, className)}>{children}</div>
)

const CardHeader = ({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) => (
  <div className={s.header}>{children}</div>
)

const CardBody = ({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) => (
  <div className={s.body}>{children}</div>
)
```

## Utility: `cn` from clsx

Always use `cn` from `clsx` for className conditionals.

```tsx
import cn from 'clsx'

const MyComponent = ({ className }: { className?: string }) => (
  <div className={cn(s.component, className)} />
)
```

## ShadCn Components

Use components from ShadCn located in `@/components/ui` when available.

```tsx
import { Card } from '@/components/ui/card'
```

